"Build a mobile app called LokaliParty using React Native Expo and Tamagui. Use the MCP context7 documentation to understand how to properly implement Tamagui components and best practices.
The app should include:
Features:

Events Discovery Screen: Display a list of upcoming local events with advanced filtering capabilities (by date, category, location, price range, event type, etc.)
Detailed Event Screen: Show comprehensive event information including description, date/time, location, capacity, organizer details, and images
Event Application System: Allow users to apply/register for events directly through the app
Advanced Filtering System: Enable multi-criteria filtering to narrow down events based on user preferences
User-Friendly Navigation: Smooth navigation between the events list, individual event details, and application screens

Technical Requirements:

Use React Native Expo for cross-platform development (iOS & Android)
Use Tamagui (with MCP context7 reference) for styling and UI components to ensure consistency and performance
Implement responsive design that adapts to different screen sizes
Follow Tamagui best practices from context7 documentation for component structure and theming"
